The paper discusses data mining and summarization of sequential data, which are topics commonly associated with the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). The use of rich patterns and description language also suggests a focus on machine learning and statistical modeling, which are covered by the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions discovering meaningful semantics, which could involve natural language processing and text analysis, covered by the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of greedy algorithms and optimization techniques suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures, which are covered by the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
